<paragraph blockId="44.[264,981,724,785]" box="[264,420,759,785]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
(
<figureCitation box="[273,412,759,785]" captionStart="FIGURES 92–98" captionStartId="45.[264,383,1290,1314]" captionTargetBox="[295,1286,291,1243]" captionTargetId="figure-167@45.[289,1371,283,1262]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="FIGURES 92–98. Robustagramma brasilense sp. nov.: 92, posterior view of male terminalia; 93, lateral view of male terminalia; 94, lateral view of male internal genitalia; 95, male sternite 5; 96, dorsal view of female terminalia; 97, ventral view of female terminalia; 98, spermathecae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5049869" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5049869/files/figure.png" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Figs. 92–98</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="44.[264,1324,839,1827]" box="[264,1032,839,865]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
As described for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cui and Marshall" authorityYear="2005" box="[465,814,839,864]" class="Insecta" family="Sphaeroceridae" genus="Robustagramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassipalpus">
<emphasis box="[465,814,839,864]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Robustagramma crassipalpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
except as follows.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="44.[264,1324,839,1827]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
Body length 2.0– 
<quantity box="[496,589,879,905]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" unit="mm" value="2.2">2.2 mm</quantity>
. General color reddish to dark brown. Face, gena, antenna and lower frons reddish yellow to brown; head otherwise dark brown. Interfrontal bristles in three pairs in addition to small interfrontal setulae. Ocellar bristle slightly longer than posterior orbital bristle, similar to outer vertical bristles. Postvertical bristles slightly convergent. Eye height 
<emphasis box="[463,490,1039,1064]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">ca</emphasis>
. 2.2–2.5 times genal height. Aristal hairs 
<emphasis box="[981,1008,1039,1064]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">ca</emphasis>
. 2.5 times as long as basal width of arista. Preapical palpal bristle distinctly longer than submedial palpal bristle, similar in length to maximum width of palpus. Prosternum with two pairs of small setulae. Acrostichal setulae in 6–8 irregular rows between anterior dorsocentral bristles. First costal sector distinctly thinner than second costal sector. Length of second costal sector 
<emphasis box="[1287,1315,1199,1224]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">ca</emphasis>
. 0.56X length of third. R twice as long as first sector of R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[976,1006,1251,1268]" fontSize="7" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">4+5</subScript>
. Fore tibiae yellow to reddish yellow. Mid tibia of male with an apicoventral bristle and several short ventral bristles on distal third; mid femur of male with a row of 6 ventral proximal bristles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="44.[264,1324,839,1827]" box="[557,587,1251,1268]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<subScript attach="left" box="[557,587,1251,1268]" fontSize="7" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">2+3</subScript>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="44.[264,1324,839,1827]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
Male terminalia: Sternite 5 twice as long as sternite 4, with a tooth­like emargination on protrudent posteromedial margin. Dorsomedial length of epandrium 
<emphasis box="[1108,1136,1401,1426]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">ca</emphasis>
. 0.4X length of sternite 8. In lateral view, surstylus slightly longer than wide.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="44.[264,1324,839,1827]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
Female terminalia: Sternite 7 longer than sternite 6, rounded posteromedially; sternite 8 completely reduced to 2 small sclerites, each articulating with a sclerite of tergite 8. Spermatheca with distal half similar in width to basal half. Paired spermathecae with long ducts, 
<emphasis box="[340,367,1601,1626]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">ca</emphasis>
. 4 times as long as spermatheca.
</paragraph>
